# WX-63 - keep the Docker build context (the HarderWare repo root) lean, and prevent a
# Windows-built bin/obj from poisoning the Linux build inside the container (the WX-62 lesson).
# Globs are **/ so nested build output at any depth is excluded, not just repo-root dirs.
**/bin/
**/obj/
**/.vs/
**/*.user
.git/
# Nothing produces release/ any more - WX-329 deleted Build-Release.ps1 - but a machine that
# ran it before then still has a WxServices\release\ tree of Windows-built publish output, and
# the context is the repo root. Kept as **/release/ (the bare `release/` this replaces lacked
# the prefix, so it only ever matched a repo-root release/ and never the one that existed).
**/release/

# Secrets / per-machine config must never enter the build context (COPY . . would otherwise sweep
# them into the build cache): the container's DB-password config and observability's Grafana admin
# password. The image carries none of these — they are bind-mounted / injected at run time.
**/appsettings.local.json
**/.env

# WX-65 - Python build/IDE cruft must not ride into the WxVis image (the WX-62 lesson, applied to
# Python): stale Windows-compiled bytecode and the VS project file. config.json is the host-only
# standalone-CLI fallback - it hardcodes .\SQLEXPRESS and C:\HarderWare\plots, so it must not ship
# in a region-agnostic image whose DB/plots settings are always injected via env vars.
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyproj
WxServices/src/WxVis/config.json
